  "text": "The HTTP/1.1 to HTTP/2 header translation in Envoy is handled across several C++ source files:\n\n## 1. Header Case Normalization (Lowercase)\n\n**`source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc`** — `ConnectionImpl::completeCurrentHeader()` (line 542–584)\nThis is the primary site of header name lowercasing. When the HTTP/1.1 parser finishes reading each header field, `completeCurrentHeader()` is called, which applies:\n```cpp\ncurrent_header_field_.inlineTransform([](char c) { return absl::ascii_tolower(c); });\n```\nThis converts all HTTP/1.1 header names to lowercase before storing them in the internal header map, making them compatible with HTTP/2's requirement for lowercase header names.\n\nThe two parsers that feed into this normalization:\n- **`source/common/http/http1/balsa_parser.cc`** — `BalsaParser::validateAndProcessHeadersOrTrailersImpl()` calls `connection_->onHeaderField()` for each header key, which eventually calls `completeCurrentHeader()`.\n- **`source/common/http/http1/legacy_parser_impl.cc`** — The legacy http-parser callbacks also call `conn_impl->onHeaderField()` and `conn_impl->onHeaderValue()`.\n\n**`source/common/http/http1/header_formatter.cc`** — `ProperCaseHeaderKeyFormatter::format()` handles optional proper-case formatting when encoding HTTP/1.1 responses (the reverse direction).\n\n## 2. Pseudo-Header Injection (:method, :path, :scheme, :authority)\n\n**`source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc`** — `ServerConnectionImpl::onHeadersCompleteBase()` (line 1186–1251)\nThis function is called when all HTTP/1.1 request headers have been parsed. It injects the pseudo-headers:\n- **`:method`** — `headers->setMethod(parser_->methodName())` (line 1218)\n- **`:path`** and **`:scheme`** — delegated to `handlePath()` (line 1215)\n\n**`source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc`** — `ServerConnectionImpl::handlePath()` (line 1100–1163)\nThis function injects:\n- **`:path`** — `headers.addViaMove(std::move(path), std::move(active_request_->request_url_))` for relative URLs, or `headers.setPath(absolute_url.pathAndQueryParams())` for absolute URLs\n- **`:scheme`** — `headers.setScheme(absl::AsciiStrToLower(absolute_url.scheme()))` for absolute URLs\n- **`:authority`** (host) — `headers.setHost(absolute_url.hostAndPort())` for absolute URLs\n\n**`source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc`** — `ConnectionManagerUtility::mutateRequestHeaders()` (line 79–290)\nThis function handles `:scheme` injection at the connection manager level:\n- If `:scheme` is not set, it sets it based on X-Forwarded-Proto or TLS status (line 208–212)\n- It also normalizes `:scheme` to lowercase: `request_headers.setScheme(absl::AsciiStrToLower(request_headers.getSchemeValue()))` (line 212)\n\n## 3. Upgrade Header Handling\n\n**`source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc`** — `ConnectionImpl::onHeadersCompleteImpl()` (line 836–940)\nHandles upgrade header processing during HTTP/1.1 parsing:\n- Detects and removes unsupported h2c upgrade headers (lines 849–870)\n- Sets `handling_upgrade_ = true` for valid upgrade requests\n- Handles CONNECT method specially (lines 872–886)\n\n**`source/common/http/utility.cc`** — Multiple upgrade transformation functions:\n- `Utility::transformUpgradeRequestFromH1toH2()` (line 1047): Converts HTTP/1.1 Upgrade requests to HTTP/2 extended CONNECT format by setting `:method` to CONNECT, setting `:protocol` to the upgrade value, and removing the `Upgrade` and `Connection` headers.\n- `Utility::transformUpgradeResponseFromH1toH2()` (line 1065): Converts HTTP/1.1 101 Switching Protocols responses to HTTP/2 200 responses, removing `Upgrade` and `Connection` headers.\n- `Utility::transformUpgradeRequestFromH2toH1()` (line 1080): Reverse direction — converts HTTP/2 extended CONNECT back to HTTP/1.1 Upgrade.\n- `Utility::transformUpgradeResponseFromH2toH1()` (line 1093): Reverse direction — converts HTTP/2 200 back to HTTP/1.1 101.\n- `Utility::isUpgrade()` (line 627): Detects upgrade requests by checking for `Upgrade` token in `Connection` header.\n\n**`source/common/http/http2/codec_impl.cc`** — `ConnectionImpl::ClientStreamImpl::encodeHeaders()` (line 274–308)\nWhen encoding requests to HTTP/2 upstream, this function calls `Http::Utility::transformUpgradeRequestFromH1toH2()` for upgrade requests, and handles CONNECT method by removing `:scheme`, `:path`, and `:protocol` headers.\n\n**`source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc`** — `ConnectionManagerUtility::mutateRequestHeaders()` and `sanitizeTEHeader()`\nFor non-upgrade requests, removes `Connection` and `Upgrade` headers (lines 92–97). For upgrade requests, these headers are preserved verbatim. Also sanitizes the `TE` header for HTTP/2 compatibility.\n\n## 4. Encoding HTTP/2 Internal Representation Back to HTTP/1.1\n\n**`source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc`** — `StreamEncoderImpl::encodeHeadersBase()` (line 138–237)\nWhen encoding HTTP/2 internal headers back to HTTP/1.1 wire format:\n- Translates `:authority` → `host` header (lines 152–156)\n- Skips all remaining `:` prefixed pseudo-headers (lines 158–161)\n\n**`source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc`** — `RequestEncoderImpl::encodeHeaders()` (line 440–507)\nEncodes the HTTP/2 internal request representation to HTTP/1.1 wire format, extracting `:method`, `:path`, and `:host` to construct the HTTP/1.1 request line.\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n- **`source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc`** — Core HTTP/1.1 codec: lowercase normalization, pseudo-header injection (:method, :path, :scheme, :authority), upgrade handling\n- **`source/common/http/http1/header_formatter.cc`** — Header key formatting (ProperCase option)\n- **`source/common/http/http1/balsa_parser.cc`** — Balsa HTTP/1.1 parser feeding into codec callbacks\n- **`source/common/http/http1/legacy_parser_impl.cc`** — Legacy http-parser feeding into codec callbacks\n- **`source/common/http/utility.cc`** — Upgrade request/response transformation functions (H1↔H2)\n- **`source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc`** — Connection manager header mutation: :scheme injection, upgrade header handling, TE sanitization\n- **`source/common/http/http2/codec_impl.cc`** — HTTP/2 codec: calls upgrade transformation when encoding to H2\n- **`source/common/http/header_utility.cc`** — Header validation utilities (checkRequiredRequestHeaders, checkValidRequestHeaders)"
